      "writtenOn": "2021-05-04T15:40:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is problematic: we\u0027re not moving the message to the destination thread, including sk_sp\u003cSkPicture\u003e ownership -- we\u0027re just writing a shallow structure.\n\nWhen exiting this scope \u0027message\u0027 gets destroyed, and as the only owner it will delete its fPicture - so the deserializing thread will pick up a stale pointer.\n\nOne way to make it work is to serialize raw SkPicture pointers and manage ownership explicitly:\n\n1) store raw SkPicture ptrs in Message instead of sk_sp\u003c\u003e\n\n2) leak/pass ownership when done recording\n\n  message.fPicture \u003d fRecorder.finishRecordingAsPicture().release();\n\n3) adopt the raw ptr on the deserialization side\n\n  sk_sp\u003cSkPicture\u003e adopted_picture(message.fPicture);",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 181,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 184,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "5f8d37d563846b367ec46e79d616c8d3d03bebc8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
